      <h2 class="pb-2 border-bottom">A summary of some scientific topics</h2>
      
    <div class="row g-5 py-5 row-cols-1 row-cols-lg-3">
      <div class="col d-flex align-items-start">
        <div>
          <h3 class="fs-2 text-body-emphasis">Art:</h3>
          <p>Art is a broad and diverse field that encompasses various forms of human expression and creativity. It involves the creation, appreciation, and interpretation of visual, auditory, or performing arts. Art plays a significant role in reflecting and shaping culture, emotions, ideas, and aesthetics. It can be classified into different mediums such as painting, sculpture, music, dance, literature, theater, film, and more. Art allows individuals to communicate, express emotions, provoke thought, challenge norms, and showcase unique perspectives.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col d-flex align-items-start">
        <div>
          <h3 class="fs-2 text-body-emphasis">Sociology:</h3>
          <p>Sociology is the scientific study of society, social relationships, human behavior, and social institutions. It focuses on understanding the patterns, structures, and processes that shape individuals and groups within a society. Sociologists explore topics such as social inequality, socialization, social norms, culture, power dynamics, social change, and various social phenomena. They conduct research, collect data, and analyze social interactions to uncover insights about the ways in which societies function, evolve, and impact individuals' lives. Sociology helps us better understand the complexities and dynamics of human societies, and often serves as a foundation for addressing social issues and promoting social justice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col d-flex align-items-start">
        <div>
          <h3 class="fs-2 text-body-emphasis">History:</h3>
          <p>History is the study of past events, civilizations, societies, and the people who lived in the past. It involves examining and analyzing primary sources, artifacts, documents, and narratives to understand their significance, causes, effects, and interconnections. The discipline of history provides insights into human experiences, societal changes, political developments, cultural shifts, technological advancements, and much more. It allows us to learn from the achievements and mistakes of the past, and provides a basis for understanding the present and envisioning the future.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  
